事发后，[[比利时首相|比利时首相]][[夏尔·米歇尔|夏尔·米歇尔]]谴责了袭击，呼吁民众保持冷静，并取消了原定的访问中国的计划。比利时全国展开为期三天的国家哀悼，民众自发展开悼念祈福的活动，全球社交网络上发起了声援比利时的活动。英国、法国、荷兰、俄罗斯、美国和欧盟等全球多个国家及国际组织的领导人及主要政治人物也对袭击表示谴责、震惊和关切，对伤亡民众表示慰问。[[美国总统|美国总统]][[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]还提出愿支援比利时打击恐怖主义。遭袭地铁站旁的[[欧盟委员会|欧盟委员会]]总部降半旗致哀，而世界各地的主要建筑物包括[[柏林|柏林]][[勃兰登堡门|勃兰登堡门]]、[[杜拜|杜拜]][[哈里发塔|哈里发塔]]、巴黎[[埃菲尔铁塔|埃菲尔铁塔]]、[[伦敦|伦敦]][[国家美术馆_(伦敦)|国家美术馆]]、[[罗马|罗马]][[特雷維噴泉|特雷維噴泉]]、[[纽约|纽约]][[世界貿易中心一號大樓|世界貿易中心一號大樓]]等均打亮[[比利时国旗|比利时国旗]]的顏色以示对该国的支持，英国[[唐宁街10号|唐宁街10号]]首相府邸则升起比利时国旗。<ref>{{cite news|last=Sheun|first=Martin|url=http://www.orangenews.hk/news/system/2016/03/23/010030035.shtml|title=【多圖】民眾廣場悼念恐襲死者 歐洲地標飄比利時國旗|publisher=橙新聞|date=2016-03-23|accessdate=2016-03-23|archive-date=2019-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506151118/http://www.orangenews.hk/news/system/2016/03/23/010030035.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Vitkovskaya|first=Julie|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2016/03/22/world-landmarks-to-light-up-in-belgian-flag-colors-after-brussels-attacks|title=Eiffel Tower lights up in Belgian flag colors after Brussels attacks|publisher=The Washington Post|date=2016-03-22|accessdate=2016-03-23|archive-date=2016-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322180023/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2016/03/22/world-landmarks-to-light-up-in-belgian-flag-colors-after-brussels-attacks/|dead-url=no}}</ref>主张限制移民的[[2016年美国总统选举|2016年美国总统选举]]候选人[[唐纳德·川普|唐纳德·川普]]和主张英国脱离欧盟的[[英国独立党|英国独立党]]都批评比利时政府和警方对安全的掌控不足，指责比利时政府的边境管制政策过于宽松，认为这种政策威胁了国家安全。川普指出应当加强边境管制，[[英国独立党|英国独立党]]则借此表示欧盟境内[[申根区|宽松的边境管制]]不利于国家的安全。<ref>{{cite news|title=「比利時像場恐怖秀」 川普：美國應關閉邊境|url=http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/1640980|publisher=自由時報|date=2016-03-22|accessdate=2016-03-22|archive-date=2016-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402163348/http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/1640980|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=布魯塞爾恐攻後 英警加強倫敦維安|url=http://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/201603220455-1.aspx|publisher=中央社|date=2016-03-22|accessdate=2016-03-22|archive-date=2016-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404231540/http://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/201603220455-1.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="GuardLive22Mar16" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.today.com/news/donald-trump-responds-brussels-attacks-it-s-very-dangerous-city-t81716|title=Donald Trump: Brussels is 'catastrophic,' waterboarding Paris suspect 'would be fine'|work=Today|date=2016-03-22|accessdate=2016-03-22|archive-date=2016-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322134021/http://www.today.com/news/donald-trump-responds-brussels-attacks-it-s-very-dangerous-city-t81716|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brussels-explosions-ukip-says-bombings-show-eu-freedom-of-movement-is-a-security-threat-a6945566.html|work=Independent|title=Brussels explosions: Ukip says terror attacks show EU freedom of movement is a 'security threat'|date=2016-03-22|accessdate=2016-03-23|archive-date=2016-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323015456/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brussels-explosions-ukip-says-bombings-show-eu-freedom-of-movement-is-a-security-threat-a6945566.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>比利时内政部长扬·庄鹏和司法部长{{le|科恩·吉恩斯|Koen Geens}}在爆炸后双双提出引咎辞职，但未获得首相夏尔·米歇尔的同意。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-belgium-blast-minister-resignation-idUKKCN0WQ19U|title=Belgian ministers offered resignation over bomb suspect|work=Reuters|date=2016-03-24|accessdate=2016-03-27|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327215717/http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-belgium-blast-minister-resignation-idUKKCN0WQ19U|dead-url=no}}</ref>

3月27日，原计划在布鲁塞尔举行的反恐游行因安全原因临时取消，有民众自发组织了悼念活动。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/brussels-march-cancelled-over-terror-fears-a6954641.html|title=Brussels march cancelled over terror fears|work=Independent|date=2016-03-27|accessdate=2016-03-27|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327011316/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/brussels-march-cancelled-over-terror-fears-a6954641.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dw.com/en/brussels-march-against-fear-cancelled-over-security-concerns/a-19144300|title=Brussels 'March Against Fear' cancelled over security concerns|work=Deutsche Welle|date=2016-03-27|accessdate=2016-03-27|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327152608/http://www.dw.com/en/brussels-march-against-fear-cancelled-over-security-concerns/a-19144300|dead-url=no}}</ref>悼念现场爆发了游行冲突，数百名反移民的[[極右翼|極右翼]]示威人群与举办悼念活动的左翼支持者在悼念现场对峙，双方互相高呼口号气氛紧张，但未发生肢体冲突。示威人群中有[[新纳粹主义|新纳粹主义]]支持者在现场行[[纳粹礼|纳粹举手礼]]，亦有[[足球流氓|足球流氓]]参与示威行动，防暴警察随即介入，以高压水枪驱散了示威人群。这是爆炸案发后首次出现右翼人士与左翼人士的大规模冲突。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rt.com/news/337355-brussels-police-memorial-far-right/|title=Riot police fire water cannon at far-right protesters at Brussels attacks memorial|work=RT.com|date=2016-03-27|accessdate=2016-03-27|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327223420/https://www.rt.com/news/337355-brussels-police-memorial-far-right/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/videos/world/2016/03/27/brussels-memorial-protest-clash-ward-cnni.cnn|title=Nazi salutes seen at attack memorial|work=CNN|date=2016-03-27|accessdate=2016-03-27|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327153232/http://edition.cnn.com/videos/world/2016/03/27/brussels-memorial-protest-clash-ward-cnni.cnn|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/brussels-attacks/right-wing-protesters-met-riot-police-brussels-memorial-site-n546206|title=Right-Wing Protesters Met by Riot Police at Brussels Memorial Site|work=NBC News|date=2016-03-27|accessdate=2016-03-27|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327150001/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/brussels-attacks/right-wing-protesters-met-riot-police-brussels-memorial-site-n546206|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="CNN Mar27">{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/03/27/europe/brussels-investigation-main/index.html|title=Nazi salutes, anti-immigrant chants disrupt Brussels memorial|work=CNN|date=2016-03-27|accessdate=2016-03-27|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327083531/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/03/27/europe/brussels-investigation-main/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

